    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Key Largo once housed a station of the famed Overseas Railroad, a key link in the early 20th‑century Florida Keys rail network.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Key_Largo%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The nearby Florida Keys National Marine Sanctuary protects 178 square nautical miles of coral reefs and marine life just off Key Largo’s coast.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        9,
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Key_Largo%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Key Largo shares its island with Tavernier to the southwest and North Key Largo to the northeast, forming a tight cluster of Keys communities.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Key_Largo%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "The marine sanctuary’s reefs extend three miles into the Atlantic, offering some of the clearest snorkeling spots in the Florida Keys.",
